'''Deep Roy''' (born [[December 1]], [[1950s#1957|1957]]) is a Kenyan-born English actor, stuntman, puppeteer and comedian of Indian ancestry who played [[Droopy McCool/Legends|Droopy McCool]] in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']]. He also played an [[Ewok]] on [[Endor]] and was a stand-in for [[R2-D2]] in some scenes. He portrayed [[Jedi Master]] [[Yoda]] for several second unit shots of the diminutive Jedi walking or standing in the open. He had to perform these scenes for [[Star Wars: Episode V The Empire Strikes Back|''The Empire Strikes Back'']] on his knees to bring him down to Yoda's height.

In the 2005 film version of ''Charlie and the Chocolate Factory'', he portrayed all of the Oompa-Loompas. He also plays the alien [[MemoryAlpha:Keenser|Keenser]] in the 2009 film ''Star Trek'' and its 2013 sequel, ''Star Trek Into Darkness''.

To sci-fi fans, he is best known for his role as [[Community:c:tardis:Mr Sin|Mr. Sin]] in the [[W:c:tardis:Doctor Who|''Doctor Who'']] serial [[W:c:tardis:The Talons of Weng-Chiang|''Talons of Weng-Chiang'']] as well as the Posicarian delegate in the later serial [[W:c:tardis:Mindwarp|''Mindwarp'']]. He was the only actor to appear in the ''Star Wars'', ''Star Trek'' and ''Doctor Who'' franchises, until [[Simon Pegg]]'s appearance in ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]''.

